    <note>Xia(2) Ni [13071] Documentation for his affinal relation to Huang(2) [13058] Bin is located in the funerary inscription for Bin's son, Le [3417]. Ni is identified in CBD as a grandson of Song [703], which is not possible. Song had only one surviving son, Anqi [698]. Anqi had only two sons, Bosun [18438] and Boqing [7237]. Bosun's sons all used radical 61 in their mingzi as the generational indicator. Therefore, in accord with chronological logic, the Xia(2) descendants of Song, who use radical 9, must be sons of Boqing. CBD, 3, 1807.</note>
